<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>arm in arm • hand in hand</xh5><p> <i>arm in arm—</i>with one’s arm under or around another person’s arm: Sally and Joan were laughing as they walked <u>arm in arm</u> down the street.</p><p><i>hand in hand—</i>1. holding hands: Molly and her stepmother wandered about in the gardens <u>hand in hand</u>, like two babes in the wood. 2. in close association: It provides a unique mix of a professionally educated workforce working <u>hand-in-hand</u> with volunteers.</p> </entry>
